cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.SY 

The paper deals with the formal modeling and analysis of web infrastructure and web applications, with a focus on security. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of "Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR), "Software Engineering" (cs.SE), "Programming Languages" (cs.PL), "Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing" (cs.DC), and "Systems and Control" (cs.SY). However, since the paper primarily focuses on security, cs.CR is the most likely category, followed by cs.SE and cs.PL.
